<div id=3D"text-fd54ab1f45" class=3D"cmp-text">
    <h2>Roulette Rules</h2>
<p><br>
The rules of roulette involve different players using different-colored chi=
ps, so that bets are not confused. The value of your chips is determined by=
 the price you pay for them. When you=E2=80=99re done playing, make sure to=
 redeem your chips at the same table where you were playing. No one will kn=
ow the value of your chips once you leave that table.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Each roulette wheel spin provides a multitude of options for the player.=
 A player may bet on single numbers, rows of numbers, or on adjacent number=
s. A player may also play colors, odd or even numbers, among others. A bet =
on a single number pays 35 to 1, including the 0 and 00. Bets on red or bla=
ck, odd or even pay 1 for 1, or even money.</p>
<p>We=E2=80=99re proud to offer Roulette in three variations. In addition t=
o our popular American-style Roulette game, which features 36 numbered slot=
s, 0, and 00, we also offer European Roulette, which has a single 0 along w=
ith the standard 36 numbers, and is a favorite among international players.=
 We also offer an exciting new version, Roulette Xtra and Lightning Roulett=
e. In these games, after =E2=80=9CNo More Bets=E2=80=9D is called, a random=
 selection of 4 or 5 numbers multiply their payouts on straight-up wagers, =
from 30 to 1 up to an impressive 200 to 1. There is also our exclusive Vene=
tian Roulette, which features a third zero space on the layout, uniquely re=
presented by the Venetian logo or a 'V'.</p>
<p>The diagram illustrates the Roulette payout rules for single-chip bets a=
nd the various combinations available to you. The dealer will be happy to e=
xplain any of them. The exact placement of the chips determines the bet bei=
ng made. Each player is responsible for positioning their wager correctly o=
n the layout, regardless of whether the bet is placed by the dealer or them=
selves.</p>

</div>

